content: I'm not sure what you are trying to say or communicate with this information. The Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) is a US government agency that regulates the securities industry, including the trading of stocks and bonds. It is not a corporation, and it does not own Norges Bank, which is the central bank of Norway. Norges Bank is an independent government agency that operates under the authority of the Norwegian Ministry of Finance. It is not affiliated with the SEC or the US government.
